# Automated Lead Monitoring System

## Overview
This project simulates a CRM-style lead tracking workflow designed to monitor sales pipeline stages and identify operational bottlenecks using Python-based automation logic.

The system tracks lead progression across multiple stages and flags inactive leads that remain stalled beyond a defined threshold period.

---

## Objectives
- Monitor lead progression across sales pipeline stages
- Identify inactive or stalled leads automatically
- Improve workflow visibility using rule-based tracking logic
- Simulate operational analytics workflows using synthetic CRM datasets

---

## Dataset Information
- Dataset Type: Synthetic CRM-style sales lead dataset
- Data Includes:
  - Lead IDs
  - Lead stages
  - Follow-up dates
  - Lead activity timelines
  - Pipeline status indicators

---

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Datetime
- Excel

---

## Methodology
1. Data Preparation & Cleaning
2. Lead Stage Monitoring
3. Date-Based Workflow Tracking
4. Inactivity Detection Logic
5. Automated Escalation Flagging
6. Operational Workflow Analysis

---

## Key Features
- Automated tracking of lead movement across pipeline stages
- Detection of leads inactive for more than 7 days
- Rule-based escalation logic for stalled leads
- Workflow visibility for operational follow-up monitoring

---

## Key Insights
- Operational tracking logic can improve lead management visibility
- Automated inactivity monitoring helps identify workflow bottlenecks
- Rule-based escalation systems support more efficient follow-up processes
- CRM workflow analytics can improve operational decision-making

